This week's deal was played in the ^*BHolkar Pairs Finals^*N at the recent ^*BIndian Bridge Nationals^*N (the 44th running of this event) in Ludhaina, India. I would like to thank ^*BT.C. Pant^*N for sending me this deal and ^*BHoney B. Prabhakar^*N, one of India's top players, for his analysis of this fascinating deal. Most deals that appear as ^*BThe Deal of the Week^*N start out with only 2 hands in view. This week's deal is not really meant to be a practical exercise so all 4 hands will be displayed right from the start. Try to figure out if the contract can be made against best defense.

I am very pleased to announce that the ^*BACBL^*N with be producing a live vugraph broadcast of the semi-finals and finals of the 2003 ^*BVanderbilt^*N through ^*BBridge Base Online^*N. As with all of the broadcasts that we make, access to this one will be ^*B100% free^*N. I am hopeful that this broadcast will be just the beginning and that we will be able to start broadcasting all of the major ACBL National events.

I would like to express my gratitude to all of the people who e-mailed the ACBL to request that they use our software for live vugraph broadcasts of their tournaments. Thanks also to the management of the ACBL for their interest in using out site for this purpose.
|
