The 2003 Vanderbilt will not take place for a few months, but we have 2 live broadcasts scheduled on ^*BBridge Base Online^*N between now and then. Our next show will take place on January 11 at 3PM EST (21:00 GMT). At that time we will broadcast an 18-board exhibition match that will commemorate the 71th anniversary of the ^*BCulbertson-Lenz Match^*N.

This exhibition match is also the work of the ACBL and, once again, I would like to thank them for choosing ^*BBridge Base Online^*N for their coverage of this event. The original Culbertson-Lenz Match was front page news when it took place and I am hoping that this exhibition match will also generate a great deal of positive publicity for our game.

We will also be producing a live broadcast of the ^*BNEC International Bridge Festival^*N that will take place in Japan in early February. The exact times and dates of this broadcast will be announced through ^*BThe Deal of the Week^*N, our web site, and ^*BBridge Base Online^*N itself as this event approaches. I normally provide live commentary and analysis during our broadcasts, but since I will be playing in the NEC tournament, I am unlikely to be available to help out with this particular live show. Other expert players will be on hand to provide their insights into the play-by-play from this prestigious tournament.

In order to watch any of these broadcasts, you will need to download and install the software for ^*BBridge Base Online^*N (which does a lot more than just allow you to watch live vugraph). The software you will need is available for ^*Bfree^*N through the following web site. Click on the blue rectangle below to be taken to this web site in a new browser window:

